column2: Mild S wind- sunny- globs of algae
Severe algal blooms all over the lake- some spots smell horrible.  From 8-20 to 8-31 lake down 4 feet
Clear day- slight breeze w. channel is disgusting- lake is disgusting- looks like prestone
Main turbidity was soil erosion from heavy rainfall.  Temp has been cool so not much algae.  Lake Level: Very high due to heavy rains
Top boards on cedar falls down.  Spillway broke- so water lowering- but there is still a lot of rain/run-off flow
Lake has experienced significant flushing in the past week due to flooding- flashboards on dam were taken out- lowering the lake level 2-3 feet from normal.
Cool weather and rainfall keeping algae down. Water-borne silt has settled out- so pretty clear
Cool weather and a lot of rainfall
Clear sunny day- still cool temps. no turbidity- more algae
Cool- not much rain- but still a lot of ground water seepage
Sunny- warm with about 3" rain in last week
A lot of rain and warm weather
Quiet bays are in #5 perception- this despite plentiful rainfall and cool weather
Cloudy- cool weather and a lot of rain
Public perception ranked 5 in quiet bays.
Public perception ranked 5 in bays.  We've had a lot of rain.
No significant rain for 2 weeks or more.
Best reading ever!  Has been cool + rainy with little run-off.
Dramatic change-10' last week-2' today.  Been up to the low 90's and no rain all week.
Had a lot of rain and we've had a lot of boat activity today.  Also it is a lot cooler.
Nice day- thick algae but not clumps.
Public perception in bays 5.  There has been a lot of rain.
Had a lot of rain and flushing for 2 weeks.
Still getting the benefit of past rain flush.
Nice 70 degree day- sunny- no wind- floating debris- no algae.
Only light rain - no run off. temp. in mid 80s.
Minor algae near windward shore- cloudy 67 degrees.
A lot for rain for flushing but not heavy enough for roiling-silt.
No wind- algae on surface- relatively heavy.
Long dry warm period. The bays are gross. Solidly in #5.
Evenings cooling down but no significant rain.
Highs in 60s-lows in 40s. Has rained but no floating effect.
Cool weather + a lot of rain.
Little rain-cool nights in 30's to low 40's.
Rain last night. Ambient air temp 65 deg F.

.8 inch rain previous 48 hours.  Diatom bloom possible causing brown color.
